name: Telluric planet #2
description:
This small planet seems to feature a very thin atmosphere, almost undistinguishable. Its poles are quite lighter in colour, probably revealing of a change in chemical composition. Could it be a sign of the presence of water in the past? Was there life on this planet? It sure seems lifeless now...
A common piece of the Celestial OBJKT collection, coming with its own cutomised container.
